# Data

Datasets, parsers, transformations, and schemas for {{PROJECT_NAME}}.

## Layout
- `raw/` - untouched source data (or pointers; large data lives elsewhere)
- `schemas/` - JSON Schema / Pydantic / type definitions for every contract
- `parsers/` - raw input -> structured output
- `samples/` - small representative fixtures used in tests and reviews

## Rules
- Every input format has a documented schema.
- Parsers are pure where possible: input in, structured output out, no side effects.
- Sample data is anonymized. No real customer/user data in source control.
- Output schemas are versioned. Breaking changes get a new version.
- Tests cover the malformed-input case for every parser.
- No large binary datasets in the repo.

